        <section id="ISKCON Temple, Juhu" class="section">
            <h2>Gateway of India</h2>
            <img src="data:image/jpeg;base64," alt="Introduction" class="section-image">
            <p>The ISKCON Temple in Juhu, Mumbai, is a prominent Hindu temple dedicated to Lord Krishna, also known as the Hare Krishna Temple. It's located on Sri Mukteshwar Devalaya Road in Juhu, near Hare Krishna Land and Juhu Beach. The temple is known for its beautiful white marble architecture, tranquil atmosphere, and spiritual activities. </p>
            <p>Location: Sri Mukteshwar Devalaya Rd, Juhu, Mumbai - 400049, near Juhu Beach and Hare Krishna Land. Architecture: White marble temple with an exquisitely carved entryway. </p>
        </section>

        <section id="Versova Beach" class="section">
            <h2>Versova Beach</h2>
            <img src="data:image/jpeg;base64," alt="About Us" class="section-image">
            <p>Versova Beach, located in the western suburbs of Mumbai, is a popular destination known for its scenic views of the Arabian Sea, a historic fishing community, and a successful beach cleanup initiative. It's a relatively clean beach, particularly compared to other Mumbai beaches, thanks to a massive cleanup effort in 2016. </p>
            <p>Location:Situated in the Andheri West area, bordering the Arabian Sea and the Versova village.Cleanliness:While once heavily polluted, it has become known for its cleanliness following a large-scale cleanup in 2016. </p>
        </section>

        <section id="Powai lake" class="section">
            <h2>Powai lake</h2>
            <img src="data:image/jpeg;base64," alt="Powai lake" class="section-image">
            <p>Powai Lake is an artificial lake in Mumbai, India, built in 1891 by damming the Mithi River between two hills. It was initially constructed to supply drinking water to the city but is now used for recreational purposes due to water quality issues. The lake is surrounded by lush greenery and is home to various birds, aquatic plants, and other wildlife. </p>
            <p>History: Built by the British to augment Bombay's water supply.Location: Situated in the Powai area of Mumbai, near IIT Bombay and NITIE (now IIM Mumbai). </p>
        </section>

        <section id="Kanheri Caves" class="section">
            <h2>Kanheri Caves</h2>
            <img src="data:image/jpeg;base64," alt="Kanheri Caves" class="section-image">
            <p>Kanheri Caves, located within Sanjay Gandhi National Park in Mumbai, is a complex of 109 rock-cut Buddhist caves, dating back to the 1st century BCE to 10th century CE. These caves, carved from basalt rock, served as monastic dwellings, meditation halls, and places of worship. The site is significant for its Buddhist architecture, including viharas (monastic residences), chaityas (prayer halls), and stupas, as well as intricate carvings and inscriptions depicting Buddhist teachings.</p>
        </section>

        <section id="Sanjay Gandhi National Park" class="section">
            <h2>Sanjay Gandhi National Park</h2>
            <img src="data:image/jpeg;base64," alt="Testimonials" class="section-image">
            <p>Sanjay Gandhi National Park, also known as Borivali National Park, is a large urban park located in Mumbai, India. It is a biodiversity hotspot with a rich history and diverse wildlife. The park is known for its Kanheri Caves, ancient Buddhist sculptures carved into the rock face. </p>
            <p>Home to a wide array of flora and fauna, including over 274 bird species, 40 mammal species, 78 reptile and amphibian species, and 170 butterfly species.Features over 1,300 plant species.The park's forests are vital for the city's water supply, with two lakes, Vihar and Tulsi, located within its boundaries.</p>
        </section>

        <section id="Madh Island" class="section">
            <h2>Madh Island</h2>
            <img src="data:image/jpeg;base64," alt="Madh Island" class="section-image">
            <p>Madh Island is a serene retreat destination, located off the coast of Mumbai, known for its beaches, fishing villages, and historical sites. It offers a mix of relaxation and cultural exploration with attractions like Madh Fort, St. Bonaventure Church, and various beaches. </p>
            <p>Madh Fort:A 17th-century Portuguese fort, Madh Fort (also known as Versova Fort) provides panoramic views of the Arabian Sea.St. Bonaventure Church: A 16th-century Portuguese church, offering a glimpse into the island's history. </p>
        </section>

        <section id="Juhu Beach" class="section">
            <h2>Juhu Beach</h2>
            <img src="data:image/jpeg;base64," alt="Contact" class="section-image">
            <p>Juhu Beach, located in Mumbai, is a popular 6-kilometer stretch along the Arabian Sea, known for its vibrant atmosphere and family-friendly activities. It's a favorite spot for locals and tourists alike, offering a mix of relaxation, entertainment, and culinary experiences</p>
            <p>Length: 6 kilometers.Location: Suburban Mumbai, accessible from various parts of the city. </p>
        </section>

        <section id="Film City" class="section">
            <h2>Film City</h2>
            <img src="data:image/jpeg;base64," alt="Film City" class="section-image">
            <p>Film City, also known as Dadasaheb Phalke Chitranagari, is a major film studio complex in Mumbai, India, established in 1977. It covers over 520 acres and is a hub for Bollywood and Marathi film production, offering various studios, sets, and support facilities. Visitors can also take guided tours to explore the film sets and learn about movie-making processes. </p>
        </section>

        <section id="Infinity Mall" class="section">
            <h2>Infinity Mall</h2>
            <img src="data:image/jpeg;base64," alt="Infinity Mall" class="section-image">
            <p>Infiniti Mall is a popular shopping and entertainment destination in Mumbai, with two locations: Andheri and Malad. Both malls offer a wide range of retail stores, dining options, and entertainment facilities. The Andheri location is known for its six-screen PVR Icon multiplex and Fun City family entertainment center. The Malad location is known for its large selection of brands and a pleasant, well-maintained environment.</p>
            <p></p>
        </section>

        <section id="Versova" class="section">
            <h2>Versova</h2>
            <img src="data:image/jpeg;base64," alt="Versova" class="section-image">
            <p>Versova is an upmarket neighborhood in northwestern Mumbai, India, known for its beach, vibrant cultural scene, and strong community spirit. It's a popular area, particularly known for the extensive clean-up effort at Versova Beach in 2016. The beach offers a serene escape with views of the Arabian Sea and sunsets. It's also part of the Mumbai North West Lok Sabha constituency.</p>
            <p></p>
        </section>
